<TITLE> Transport strike in Barisal snaps link on 19 routes </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Barisal, Oct 2 (bdnews24.com)--Transport workers in Barisal have started a wildcat strike protesting at the arrests of two co-workers, snapping communication on 19 routes of Barisal, Patuakhali, Bhola, Barguna, Pirojpur and Jhalakathi districts, police said on Friday. Kotwali police chief Nuruzzaman Chowdhury told bdnews24.com said the strike started soon after two bus assistants were arrested from Rupatali Terminal in Barisal. He said a bus was carrying passengers, including two magistrates Mohammad Abul Bashar and Mrityunjoy Mistri, on a rough road. The passengers, including the two magistrates, asked the bus driver to drive slow and at one stage an argument ensued with the bus driver and his two assistants, he said. Mistri later informed the police of the incident in details and 'Majed' and 'Sumon', the assistants, were detained, he said. However, the bus driver managed to escape the scene, Chowdhury said and added the arrestees were in police custody. Sultan Mahmud, general secretary of Barisal District Transports Workers' Union, said they would continue with the strike until the two were freed bdnews2
